      "site_admin": false
    },
    "body": "Previously, `get_routing_method_type()` returned `DeepSeekV3` for any sigmoid-scored model with top_k > 1, regardless of whether the model actually uses grouped expert routing. This caused crashes in the flashinfer TRTLLM kernel for models like MiniMax-M2.1 that has no expert groups (`num_expert_group=None`). \n\nThis PR fixes the error by assigning it to `RoutingMethodType.Unspecified` when there is no `num_expert_group`\n\nRelated to: https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/issues/34622, https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/issues/34477, https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/pull/34494\n\ncc: @jeejeelee @haosdent @NickLucche \n\n## Test\nLaunching a server on MiniMaxAI/MiniMax-M2.1 \n### Before this PR\n```\nRuntimeError: Worker failed with error 'Check failed: (args->n_group != 0) is false: n_group should not be zero for DeepSeekV3 routing', please check the stack trace above for the root cause\n```\n\n### After this PR\nServer spin up correctly",
    "created_at": "2026-02-17T06:30:52Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-02-19T18:26:13Z",
    "closed_at": "2026-02-18T21:03:25Z",
